<HEADLINE> 6 Killed, 45 Injured in Road Accident in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Six people were killed and 45
others injured when a coach fell off a bridge on Dhaka-Aricha
Highway Saturday evening in Manikgonj, some 70 kilometers west of
Dhaka, police said.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred when the coach broke the railings of the
bridge.
</P>
<P>
The injured were sent to hospitals in Manikgonj and Dhaka.
</P>
