<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two Bangladeshis Killed by Indian Border Troops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Two Bangladeshi citizens were
killed and 10 others injured when Indian Border Security Forces (
BSF) opened fire Saturday at village Baitta Nagar of Feni district,
some 150 kilometers southeast of Dhaka.
</P>
<P>
According a report of the official Bangladesh News Agency, two
of the injured were admitted to a Feni hospital, while the others
were released after receiving first aid in a local health complex.
</P>
<P>
Personnel of the Bangladesh Rifles rushed to the scene from
Feni and tension was prevailing in the area.
</P>
<P>
The report said an Indian citizen Wednesday accused some
Bangladeshis of stealing his cow and then a group of Indian
citizens with the support of the BSF entered the Bangladeshi
territory Friday and forcibly took away seven cows of Bangladeshi
villagers.
</P>
<P>
The situation in the area worsened Saturday when more than 100
Indian citizens with the support of the BSF entered the
Bangladeshi territory and attacked the Bangladeshi villagers,
which later resulted in a clash between them.
</P>
<P>
Then the BSF fired indiscriminately on the Bangladeshi
villagers, killing two Bangladeshis and injuring 10 others, the
report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
