<HEADLINE> Arafat to Meet Jordanian King Abdullah, Egyptian President Mubarak </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of Palestinian National
Authority (PNA) Yasser Arafat will meet Jordanian King Abdullah Bin
Hussein here on Monday and Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak in
Cairo on Tuesday, said a PNA senior official here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The meetings will take place on the eve of Arafat's visit to
Washington that starts on April 20, according to Arafat's adviser
Nabil Abu-Rudeinah.
</P>
<P>
The talks between Arafat and King Abdullah will focus on the
latest developments of the Palestinian-Israeli peace process and
the ways of supporting the Palestinian stance in the peace talks
especially before the summit between Arafat and U.S. President Bill
Clinton.
</P>
<P>
King Abdullah's visit to Gaza is "highly important and falls
within the framework of continuous coordination and consultation
between Palestine and Jordan," Abu-Rudeinah said.
</P>
<P>
This is the second visit to Gaza by King Abdullah since he
assumed the throne in 1998. He last visited Gaza in 1999.
</P>
<P>
On his way to Washington, Arafat will stop over in Cairo on
Tuesday and consult with Mubarak, the PNA official added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Abu-Rudeinah said Arafat will receive Omani Minister
of State for Foreign Affairs Yousef Bin Alawi Bin Abdullah who will
convey to him a message from Omani Sultan Qaboos Bin Said on the
Middle East and the bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
The PNA official underscored the importance of conducting an
Arab appraisal of the peace talks, pointing out that the Washington
talks between Israel and the Palestinians have failed so far to
make any headway.
</P>
<P>
He also underlined the importance of Arab-U.S. coordination and
consultation to push forward the peace process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
