<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuwaiti Emir, Lebanese President Discuss Boosting Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Kuwaiti Emir Sheikh Jaber Al-
Ahmed Al-Sabah on Sunday met with visiting Lebanese President Emile
Lahoud on ways of boosting bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
The talks also touched upon a wide-range of important issues of
mutual concern, the Kuwait News Agency reported. But it didn't go
into further details about the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Earlier reports by the agency said the Kuwaiti-Lebanese talks
should cover the latest developments in the Middle East peace
process, especially Israel's planned withdrawal from South Lebanon
by next July and its possible repercussion.
</P>
<P>
Before the bilateral talks, Lahoud received the Lebanese
community in his residence at Bayan Palace, Kuwait's state guest
house.
</P>
<P>
In the meeting, Lahoud told the Lebanese that his visit is to "
express gratitude to the state of Kuwait for its support to Lebanon
against the Israeli aggression. "
</P>
<P>
"We cannot forget the Kuwaiti Parliament's decision to back
Lebanon against the recent Israeli attacks," he said.
</P>
<P>
On Israel's possible withdrawal, Lahoud said "Israel tries to
claim that we are against the pullback. On the contrary, we are
with implementation of all international resolutions relevant to
the unconditional return of Lebanese and Arab rights."
</P>
<P>
"We cannot accept to safeguard the security of Israel and to
shoulder responsibility from the problem that resulted from the
displacement of thousands of Palestinians in South Lebanon," he
added.
</P>
<P>
Lahoud arrived here earlier Sunday for a two-day official visit.
He is now on a seven-nation tour, which is designed to rally
support to force Israel to halt constant attacks on Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
He has visited Saudi Arabia and will travel to the United Arab
Emirates, Qatar, Bahrain, Egypt and Iran. 
</P>
</TEXT>
