<HEADLINE> 150 Tons of Relief Food Airlifted to Gode, Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The International Committee
of Red Cross (ICRC) announced here Sunday that it has airlifted
about 150 tons of relief food to drought-affected people in Gode,
Ethiopia in the past four days.
</P>
<P>
ICRC delegation head for Ethiopia Yves Giovannoni told a press
 conference that his committee was airlifting 15 to 17 tons of
relief assistance daily through its Hercules C-130 plane to Gode,
some 600 km southeast of Addis Ababa.
</P>
<P>
The assistance provided by the ICRC for the first two months of
the operation represents a total of 4,512 tons, he said.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that Ethiopia, with more than eight million
people suffering from starvation, needs about 900,000 tons of
relief food to feed its drought-affected and internally displaced
people during this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
