<HEADLINE> UN to Spend $2.7 Million to Upgrade Djibouti's Port </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations is due to
spend 6.9 million U.S. dollars to develop Djibouti's port and
roads this year in an urgent effort to bring in enough food to
avert famine in Ethiopia, Ethiopian News Agency reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Of all the stated sum of money, 2.7 million U.S. dollars will
be used to improve port facilities.
</P>
<P>
Following the implementation of the UN plan, the handling
capacity of the port of Djibouti will increase to 145,000 tons a
month from around 100, 000 now, the mass media said.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the United Nations will also spend 4.2 million U.S.
dollars to upgrade the two main roads leading to Ethiopia, and to
bring in 400 trucks from abroad to help deliver food around
Ethiopia. 
