<HEADLINE> S.African Minister Wants to Convey Correct Anti-AIDS Message </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Music and dance are perfect
vehicles to convey AIDS awareness to people in rural areas, South
African Home Affairs Minister Mangosuthu Buthelezi said on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
He told competitors of the African Cultural Music and Dance
Association HIV/AIDS competition in Soweto, Johannesburg that
these forms of expression could tell the story of the AIDS
epidemic to illiterate people or those who did not have
information resources available to them.
</P>
<P>
"Through every song performed and every musical piece
presented, through every dance and every subtle movement, the
truth is being spoken about the devastation of the HIV/AIDS
epidemic," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Even television and radio are not widely accessible. If we
are to get the message of HIV/AIDS into these communities, we must
choose a means which conveys the truth directly from person to
person."
</P>
<P>
Music and dance would increase AIDS awareness in rural
communities, traditional groups in townships and inner city
hostels who were key to the success of the AIDS campaign,
Buthelezi was quoted by South African Press Association as
saying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
