<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore's Retail Sales Drop in February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Singapore's total retail sales
value dropped to 1.919 billion Singapore dollars (1.122 billion U.
S. dollars) in February this year, plunging by 33.8 percent
compared with the previous month, the Singapore Department of
Statistics (SDS) said in its monthly bulletin.
</P>
<P>
But the February figure was 9.9 percent higher over the same
month of 1999 and excluding motor vehicles, the retail index in
February shrank by 22.9 percent over January, SDS said.
</P>
<P>
SDS said almost all retail activities reported lower sales in
February, with retailers of food and beverages and furniture and
household equipment leading others by experiencing significantly
slower business of 42.1 percent and 36 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
The bulletin shows that except telecommunication and computers
which registered a slight increase of 0.6 percent in February, all
other retail activities recorded double-digit contractions in
sales.
</P>
<P>
SDS attributed February's sharp drop mainly to declining motor
vehicles sales which plunged by 50.1 percent over January, and the
shorter month of February.
</P>
<P>
SDS also said the overall catering trade index in February
declined by 2.3 percent over January but rose by 6.3 percent
compared with the same month of 1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
