<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Websites Join Hands to Protect Tibetan Antelopes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Several well-known Chinese
websites entered a web alliance today to protect the Tibetan
antelopes from extinction.
</P>
<P>
The websites include Chinaren.com and east.cn.net, whose fund-
raising and international co-operation activities are supported by
university students in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The Tibetan antelope, one of the top priorities on China's
protected species list, is an endangered species. The animals live
in the grassland in and around Qinghai, the Xinjiang Uygur
Autonomous Region and Tibet Autonomous Region. They are usually
found in the mountains between 3,700 and 5,500 meters high.
</P>
<P>
According to wildlife experts, the number of Tibetan antelopes
has fallen from about 50,000 to 75,000 in 1995 to the present 30,
000.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000416.0045 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People's Daily: What Is Lu Up To ? (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 16 (Xinhua) -- People's Daily, the leading
Chinese newspaper, will carry an observer's article revealing the
true purpose of the statements made by Taiwan's Annette Lu in her
interview with a Hong Kong cable TV in which she advocated "
independence" for the island.
</P>
<P>
The article says that Lu advocated separatism between the
Taiwan people and the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
"No matter where Chinese come from, be that Beijing, Shanghai
or Taiwan, we are all Chinese and members of the big family of
Chinese nation," the article says.
</P>
<P>
Lu's allegation denies that Taiwan is an inseparable part of
China and that the people of Taiwan are an inseparable part of the
Chinese nation, the article says.
</P>
<P>
Lu attempted to provoke animosity between the people on both
sides of the Taiwan Straits by calling Taiwan people the "
scapegoats of a civil war between Kuomintang and the Communist
Party of China", the article says.
</P>
<P>
The temporary separation of Taiwan and the mainland cannot
change the fact that there is only one China in the world and that
Taiwan is part of China, the article says, and the separation will
inevitably come to an end.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan's future resides in its reunification with the
motherland, the article says. The separatists' attempts to
separate Taiwan from the motherland will do harm to the
fundamental interests of the entire Chinese nation including the
people in Taiwan, it says.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000416.0046 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People's Daily: What Is Lu Up To ? (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lu alleged that the relationship between the mainland and
Taiwan should be that of "remote relatives" in terms of history
and when geographical factors are considered, they are "close
neighbors," according to the article.
</P>
<P>
It is internationally acknowledged that there is only one China,
the article says. Over 160 countries have set up diplomatic ties
with China, and they all recognize that Taiwan is an inalienable
part of China, and the government of the People's Republic of
China is the sole legitimate government of China, the article says.
"The question facing us now is how to let Taiwan return to the
motherland at an early date, and realize the reunification of the
motherland," it says.
</P>
<P>
The article says that on the one hand, Lu drummed up Taiwan's "
independence", and on the other hand, she called for talks to
communicate with the mainland. Lu has contradicted herself because
the Chinese Government has stressed again and again that the one-
China principle is the prerequisite for any talks across the
Straits. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000416.0047 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Business Summit 2000 Convenes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 16 (Xinhua)-- The China Business Summit 2000,
jointly sponsored by the World Economic Forum and the China
Enterprise Confederation, opened today in Beijing with
representatives from over 600 Chinese and overseas businesses
participating.
</P>
<P>
Chinese president Jiang Zemin and Chairman of the National
People's Congress Standing Committee Li Peng sent their scriptures
to congratulate the opening of the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Li Rongrong, vice minister of the State Economic and Trade
Commission, said at the opening ceremony that with China's
imminent entry into the WTO, the country will become fully
integrated into the global economy.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, he said, China is bound to create enormous business
opportunities for both Chinese and overseas businesses.
</P>
<P>
During the three-day summit, business representatives will
discuss globalization and WTO's influence on the Chinese economy,
strategies for opening up the western regions, and how information
industry will transform businesses in China.
</P>
<P>
The World Economic Forum is non-governmental international
organization based in Geneva. The organization has over 1,000
businesses worldwide. Since 1981, the organization has sponsored
an international business forum every year in cooperation with the
China Enterprise Confederation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
