<HEADLINE> Egyptian, Jordanian Leaders Discuss Mideast Peace Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak met
visiting Jordanian King Abdullah Bin Hussein Sunday to examine
the "difficult" conditions on the three tracks of the Middle East
peace process.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Information Minister Safwat el Sharif said the Mubarak-
Abdullah meeting came within the context of consultations, exchange
of views and coordination between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He also said Abdullah, who arrived here earlier in the day, has
returned to Jordan after a brief visit.
</P>
<P>
The situation in the Middle East was the focal topic of their
discussions in light of the difficult conditions the peace process
is experiencing on its three tracks, he said.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders examined the problems and stumbling blocks as
well as the views of the various parties concerned, he added.
</P>
<P>
The visit came amid a flurry of diplomatic activity in the
region linked to Israeli plans to carry out a unilateral military
withdrawal from Lebanon by July. 
</P>
