<HEADLINE> Indian Troops Repulse Militant Attack In Kashmir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 16 (Xinhua) -- India said on Sunday that its
troops repulsed a militant attack on their camp Saturday evening,
killing three top militants belonging to Hizbul Mujahideen, an
active Muslim group in the disputed Kashmir, while an equal number
of its special police officers died in militancy-related violence
in the area.
</P>
<P>
The Press Trust of India (PTI) reported in Kashmir that Indian
troops returned fire Saturday night when a group of militants
attacked an army camp at Achabal in Ananthaq district.
</P>
<P>
The PTI quoted an official spokesman as saying that one
militant was killed in the fighting while three top militants of
the outlawed hizbul Mujahideen were killed in another gunfight
between Indian security forces and "ultras" in Handwara of Kupwara
district.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the PTI said, eight people, including three special
police officers, were killed when militants attacked Indian
security forces during search operations in Mandi sector of Poonch
in Kashmir. 
</P>
