<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rainstorm Wrecks Havoc in Southern Guangdong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 16 (Xinhua)-- A heavy rainstorm in the past
two days has killed eight people and cost 200 million yuan in
damages in south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
Floods inundated Zhuhai, Shenzhen, Zhongshan and other areas
along the Pearl River Delta from April 13-14 disrupting traffic
and causing landslides.
</P>
<P>
The floods have abated and rain stopped yesterday. Despite the
disaster, the rainstorm alleviated drought in much of the region,
said experts. 
</P>
