<DOCNO> XIE20000416.0071 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Minor Planet Named After Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At the ceremony, Lu Yongxiang, president of CAS, presented a
certification of the naming to Edmund Ho Hau Wah, chief executive
of the Macao SAR.
</P>
<P>
The minor planet was discovered by the Beijing Observatory
under CAS in January 1997. It was given the permanent number of
8423 by the international Minor Planet Center on March 13, 1998.
</P>
<P>
In June 1998, the Beijing Observatory applied to the Minor
Planet Center for naming the minor planet after Macao, which was
to return to the motherland and become a Special Administrative
Region of China on December 20, 1999. The application was approved
in October 1998.
</P>
<P>
"The naming of the minor planet brings about great honor to the
Macao SAR," Edmund Ho said at the ceremony. "The honor comes from
the people of the motherland, and from Chinese scientists' love
for Macao." 
</P>
</TEXT>
