reduced the chances for a time close to Rotterdam's best of 2:06.
50 ran by Belayneh Densamo of Ethiopia in 1988.
</P>
<P>
In the women's race, which two years ago saw a world record
when Tegla Loroupe of Kenya won in 2:20:47, was won in 2:30:21 by
36-year-old Ana Isabel Alonso of Spain, reports said. 
