<HEADLINE> Fact File of London Marathon Winner Pinto </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Following is the profile of
Portuguese Antonio Pinto, who won the men's London marathon on
Sunday:
</P>
<P>
Born: Amarante, Portugal, March 22, 1966.
</P>
<P>
Clocked fifth fastest time ever with his two hours six minutes
36 minutes in the 2000 London marathon, breaking compatriot Carlos
Lopes' 15-year-old European record of 2:07:12.
</P>
<P>
Has now won the London event three times and has never finished
outside the top three in his six appearances in the world's best
big city marathon.
</P>
<P>
Won the 1994 Berlin marathon and the 1998 Lisbon half marathon
in a then world best of 59 minutes 43 seconds. Later that year won
the European 10,000 meters title and held the European 10,000
meters record briefly last year with a time of 27 minutes 12.47
seconds.
</P>
</TEXT>
