<HEADLINE> Fact File of London Marathon Winner Loroupe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Following is the fact file of
Tegla Loroupe, winner of the women's London marathon on Sunday:
</P>
<P>
Born: Kaponguria, Kenya, November 6 1970.
</P>
<P>
First made her mark in 1993 Stuttgart world championships with
fourth place in 10,000 meters final.
</P>
<P>
Debut win in 1994 New York marathon and finished first again
following year.
</P>
<P>
Broke Norwegian Ingrid Kristiansen's 1985 world best of two
hours 21 minutes six seconds when she clocked 2:20:47 in the 1998
Rotterdam marathon, assisted by male pacemakers. Reduced that mark
to 2:20:43 in Berlin last year, again paced by men.
</P>
<P>
Has won three half-marathon titles and finished third in last
year's Seville world championships 10,000 meters in a Kenyan
record 30:23.03.
</P>
