<HEADLINE> Shanghai Launching Cancer Prevention Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai started a week long
publicity drive on cancer prevention Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Disease Prevention and Control Center issued an
hour long educational video teaching people how to detect liver,
stomach, breast and intestinal cancer at the early stages.
</P>
<P>
The number of cancer patients increases by 32,000 every year in
Shanghai. Over 23,000 people die of cancer every year. One in
every four cancer patients die for the disease.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest statistics, cancer has become the No.1
killer among people aged 15-64 in Shanghai. However, doctors say
that about one third of the patients can be cured if the disease
is found at the early stage.
</P>
<P>
Major hospitals in Shanghai will take part in the cancer
prevention campaign. 
</P>
</TEXT>
