<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Central Chinese Province Opens Trade Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Henan, the most populous
province in central China, opened its trade fair for the year 2000
today, drawing more than 1,000 people from 43 countries and
regions at the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The three-day trade fair, jointly sponsored by the People's
Government of Henan Province and the China Council for the
Promotion of International Trade, will offer more than 500
projects for overseas businesspersons with the investment expected
to exceed one billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Henan is known for its abundant land, mineral and labor
resources.
</P>
<P>
Present at today's opening ceremony were businesspeople from
Canada, Japan, the Republic of Korea and representatives from the
Henan's sister provinces abroad and diplomatic envoys in China.
</P>
</TEXT>
