<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Top Legal News Items This Week in China (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 16 (Xinhua) -- From today on, Xinhua will
release a weekly review of legal events in China to offer readers
a comprehensive perspective of what is happening in the legal
field in the country.
</P>
<P>
 3,632 Citizen-vs.-Government Cases Reported in Past Decade
in Beijing
</P>
<P>
People's courts at various levels in Beijing accepted and heard
3,632 citizen-vs.-government cases during 1990-1999.
</P>
<P>
Among these, 3,616 cases were concluded, and the citizens won
in 832 cases.
</P>
<P>
The cases concerned all sorts of administrative acts involving
patents, trademarks, land and mineral resources, foreign
investment, supervision over pharmaceuticals, management of state
assets, unfair competition, urban planning, education, and the
press and publications.
</P>
<P>
 Crocodile Bites
</P>
<P>
La Chemise Lacoste, the France-based producer of men's shirts,
brought a Hong Kong-based garment company to court in Beijing on
April 11 for violation of a registered trade mark: a crocodile.
</P>
<P>
La Chemise Lacoste charged that without permission from La
Chemise Lacoste, Hong Kong-based Crocodile Garments Limited and
its agent in Beijing used its crocodile trade mark on similar
products, claimed compensation of 3.5 million yuan (about 421,600
U.S. dollars), and demanded an open apology from the Hong Kong
crocodile.
</P>
<P>
Policeman Killed While Searching for Abducted Women
</P>
<P>
A 31-year-old Chinese policeman of Mongolia nationality was
killed on April 11 while searching for kidnapped women in a
village in north China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The policeman, Sainbair, was the first police officer killed in
the line of duty since the nationwide hunt for traffickers of
women and children kicked off on April 1 this year.
</P>
<P>
In another development, a convicted kidnapper, Liang Kunmin,
was given the death sentence by a local court in east China's
Jiangsu Province on April 14 for abduction and rape of five women.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
