<HEADLINE> Chinese President Concludes Visit to Palestine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BETHLEHEM, Palestine, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President
Jiang Zemin left here Sunday morning, winding up his state visit to
Palestine.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the trip, the first by a Chinese head of state, at
the invitation of Palestinian President Yasser Arafat.
</P>
<P>
Arafat saw Jiang off at the presidential office. He told Jiang
that the visit itself shows Chinese government and Chinese people's
strong support to the just cause of Palestinian people.
</P>
<P>
Jiang expressed thanks for the hospitality accorded him by
Arafat and Palestinian people. He said the warm and friendly
reception demonstrates Palestinian peoples' friendship with Chinese
people.
</P>
<P>
Palestine is the second leg of Jiang's five-nation visit. The
other four countries are Israel, Turkey, Greece and South Africa.
</P>
