<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World's Longest Serving Ruler Dies in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The Raja (King) of Malaysia'
s northern state of Perlis, the world's longest serving ruler,
passed away Sunday at the age of 79, Bernama News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Tuanku Syed Putra Jamalullail, the Raja of Perlis since
December 1945, was admitted to the National Heart Institute here
on March 21 for heart problem, kidney complications and diabetes.
</P>
<P>
The announcement of his death was made by Perlis Chief Minister
Shahidan Kassim in Kangar, the state capital, Bernama said.
</P>
<P>
He was installed as the third Yang di-Pertuan Agong (Supreme
Head of State) On January 4, 1961. 
</P>
</TEXT>
