<DOCNO> XIE20000416.0114 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clan Fighting flares Up in Somalia, Killing Eight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 16 (Xinhua) - Rival Somali tribesmen exchanged
gunfire Saturday, killing at least eight and wounding 15, in a
battle for territory near Brava, a small port 200 kilometers south
of Mogadishu, capital of Somalia, reports reaching here said
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Local residents were quoted as saying Sunday that the fighting
erupted after local elders failed to reconcile the two groups.
</P>
<P>
They did not give more details.
</P>
<P>
The fighting cut the flow of aid supplies to famine-hit areas
of Bay, Bakol and Gedo, further south of the Somali capital.
</P>
<P>
Security guards protecting a food aid convoy returned fire when
it was intercepted near Brava, killing one man and wounding two
others, said the reports.
</P>
<P>
However, the convoy of 30 trucks loaded with food aid was able
to resume its journey Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Horn of Africa country has been hard hit by drought this
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
