<HEADLINE> India Wins Four Nations Hockey Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 16 (Xinhua) -- India scored a last-minute goal
to beat European champions Germany, winning a Four Nations field
hockey tournament in Perth on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
With seconds remaining, Dhanraj Pillay scored his second goal
for a 3-2 win after Germany scored first in the 20th minute
through Matthias Witthaus and Pillay equalised in the 31st minute.
</P>
<P>
India overtook the lead when Dilip Tirkey converted his penalty
corner strike in the 57th minute before Bjorn Michel equalised
after 68 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Germany beat India 2-1 in the tournament.
</P>
<P>
"This win means that our Olympic campaign is now well on track,
" India coach V. Baskaran said. 
