<HEADLINE> PAL, Lufthansa Start Joint Cargo Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Philippine Airlines (PAL) and
Lufthansa German Airlines started Sunday a joint cargo service
under an agreement signed by the two sides recently.
</P>
<P>
According to a report by the Philippine News Agency, the
agreement permits PAL to block space on Lufthansa's twice-a-week
cargo flights between Manila and Frankfurt.
</P>
<P>
PAL can then sell this space to accommodate cargo moving
between the Philippines and Germany, as well as on the Manila-
Bankok leg of Lufthansa's cargo service, it said.
</P>
<P>
The joint service started Sunday using the German airline's MD-
11 freight aircraft, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
Cargo operations is one of PAL's major business units,
accounting for about 12 percent of the airline's operating
revenues.
</P>
<P>
But PAL has been absent from the European market since June
1998, when it was forced to suspend regular services to Frankfurt,
Paris and London in the aftermath of the Asian crisis in that year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
