<HEADLINE> Festival Road Death Toll Declines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bangkok, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The number of highway accident
death during the Thai festival period of Songkran (April 12 to 14)
reached 29, declining from last year's total of 53, the Bangkok
Post reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
It said 152 people had also been injured in 37 road accidents
during this Songkran festival.
</P>
<P>
Road casualties during the festival period are declining these
years.
</P>
<P>
Last year, 53 people were killed, down from 98 in 1998 and 137
in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Thai Authorities attributed the yearly reduction to a drastic
crackdown on drunk drivers. 
</P>
