<HEADLINE> Minor Communal Conflict Erupts in North Maluku, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 16 (Xinhua) -- At least three persons were
killed and two others injured in a minor communal clash in
Halmahera island in North Maluku, Indonesia, on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The renewed conflict happened in the northern part of Galela
sub-district, about 2,600 kilometers northeast of Jakarta,
according to the Antara News Agency Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Rioters, who reportedly used a small boat to the northern
seashore of Galela sub-district in the evening, had moved
undetected by Marine Corps personnel deployed in the Morotai
island.
</P>
<P>
The three fatalities in the unrest had reportedly been killed
by a molotov cocktail and other sharp weapons. The material losses
as a consequence of the clashes were still unknown as the scenes
of the fighting were not easily accessible.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, in two villages in Jailolo sub-district in the
northern part of Halmahera, people's homes continued to be the
target of arson.
</P>
<P>
"The unrest in the two villages erupted last week when an
identified mass torched 22 houses and one house of worship in
Tauro Besar village and one house in Tauro Kecil village," Capt.
Afson Sirat, field operations officer at the North Maluku Military
Command was quoted by Antara as saying.
</P>
<P>
But on the whole, he said, there was no major security
disturbance in the North Maluku province and the local
administrations were meeting no hindrance in implementing their
administrative, development and social programs.
</P>
<P>
The situation in general remains good on the islands in the
province and all activities are taking place unperturbed, he added.
</P>
<P>
Maluku has witnessed a year long ethnic bloodshed between
Christian and Muslim, which has claimed more than 1,300 civilians.
The security situation in the area had gradually returned to
normal this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
