<HEADLINE> Largest Shipboard Drug-Smuggling Case Uncovered </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The Dalian Customs Office in
northeast China's Liaoning Province recently captured all five
suspects involved in the largest shipboard drug-trafficking case
in the country's history.
</P>
<P>
Customs officials discovered 100 kg of the drug "ice" on board
the Bingcheng-508 docked in the Dalian harbor.
</P>
<P>
Suspicion was raised when the cargo was declared to be 16.7
tons of refined salt heading for Japan, officials said, pointing
out that China seldom exports such amount of salt there. They
searched the ship and discovered the drug packed in seven boxes.
</P>
<P>
A total of 420,000 US dollars was also found hidden on the ship,
the officials reported. 
</P>
