<HEADLINE> Chinese Securities Brokers Go On-line </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Two Chinese securities brokers,
Qinghai Securities Co. and Huatai Securities Co., recently
announced the opening of their on-line stock trading systems.
</P>
<P>
Qinghai Securities, based in Qinghai Province in western China,
will provide on-line brokerage services through its website: www.
my0578.com.
</P>
<P>
A relatively small brokerage, the company plans to transform
itself into the first in China with on-line trading as its main
business.
</P>
<P>
Zhong Xiaojian, general manager of Qinghai Securities, said his
company is trying to create a new way of developing for a small
brokerage in an increasingly competitive market.
</P>
<P>
Huatai Securities Company, a broker-dealer based in Nanjing in
east China's Jiangsu Province, is engaging in on-line trading
through its website: www.htsc.com.cn, which opened a month ago.
</P>
<P>
The company claims that over the past month it has attracted 40,
000 on-line customers and brokered 100 million yuan in on-line
trading, accounting for 10 percent of its total brokerage value
for the period. 
