<HEADLINE> China's Motorcycle Output and Exports Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 16 (Xinhua)-- China produced 1.648 million
motorcycles in the first two months this year, up 26 percent on a
yearly basis, according to a State Administration of Machinery
Industry report.
</P>
<P>
China sold 1.617 million motorcycles during the two months, an
increase of 13 percent.
</P>
<P>
These figures include 1.594 million two-wheeled motorcycles, a
rise of 26 percent over a year ago, and 54,000 three-wheeled
motorcycles, an increase of 11 percent.
</P>
<P>
The sector exported 60,000 motorcycles in February alone, up
372 percent over the same month last year, earning 30.62 million
US dollars.  
</P>
