<DOCNO> XIE20000416.0193 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiangsu to Boost Pharmaceutical Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Jiangsu Province, one of China's
economic powerhouses, plans to boost its pharmaceutical industry
in the years to come.
</P>
<P>
According to the plan, the industry's gross output value will
reach 21.5 billion yuan this year, up 15.6 percent; the commercial
sales value, 13 billion yuan, up 11 percent; and the industrial
and commercial profits and tax payment, 2.5 billion yuan, up 10
percent; and goods delivered for export, three billion yuan, up 1.
538 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the east China Province's pharmaceutical
industry ranks the country's third in output value and profit.
Besides, Jiangsu has a large medicine market with its sales volume
accounting for 8.5 percent of the country's total.
</P>
<P>
At present, the industry has some 200 enterprises with fixed
assets totaling four billion yuan, and employs 130,000 people.
</P>
<P>
These enterprises are mainly located in Suzhou, Wuxi and
Changzhou cities in southeastern Jiangsu. They pay attention to
science and technology and export-oriented production, and sell
more than 1,000 varieties of drugs on the international market.
The export of Vitamin C alone tops 10,000 tons a year.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu's pharmaceutical industry generated an output value of
18.5 billion yuan in 1999, ranking third in the country, with the
added value reaching 4.91 billion yuan, up 22.52 percent. It
realized an industrial sales income of 11.95 billion yuan, up 10.
34 percent. Its gross industrial output value and sales income
ranked seventh in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
