<DOCNO> XIE20000416.0194 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jilin's Pharmaceutical Industry Posts Fast Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Jilin Province in northeast
China has reported fast growth in its pharmaceutical industry, one
of the pillars of local economy.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the industry currently has 390
pharmaceutical enterprises and more than 100 medical instrument
plants.
</P>
<P>
The gross output value of the pharmaceutical industry totaled 7.
02 billion yuan in 1999, up 24.62 percent over 1998; the profits
came to 708 million yuan, up 12.3 percent; and the gross sales
value amounted to 1.69 billion yuan, up 66.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
The gross output value of the pharmaceutical industry is
expected to reach nine billion yuan this year, up 28.18 percent
over 1999; the industrial added value will be 2.9 billion yuan, up
16 percent; and the gross sales revenue will reach 6.7 billion
yuan, up 33.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
Jilin's pharmaceutical industry includes chemical drugs, TCM
drugs, medical instruments and medicinal packaging. The output
value of chemical and patent drugs accounts for 90 percent of the
industry's total.
</P>
<P>
The industry is making full use of local resources of herbal
resources in the Changbai mountain range, raw materials of fine
chemicals and maize to develop synthetic drugs, bio-medicine and
TCM drugs.
</P>
<P>
It plans to modernize the production of traditional Chinese
medicine and develop preparations with high efficiency, clear
elements and quality standard. 
</P>
</TEXT>
