<HEADLINE> Man United Move Closer to Premier League Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Defending champions Manchester
United took another big step towards English premier league title
with a 4-0 win over Sunderland on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Man United, who started the day effectively needing seven
points for the crown, stretched their lead over second-played
Liverpool to 14 points with just five games to play.
</P>
<P>
Ole Gunnar Solksjaer scored two goals for the winners in the
day's match. He pounced on a poor backpass to score in the second
minute and then showed great composure to put away his second in
the 51st minute, dancing around a defender and firing in with his
left foot.
</P>
<P>
Nicky Butt smashed in a fierce shot from the right-hand side of
the box for the third in the 66th minute and Henning Berg added a
fourth in the 70th as Sunderland went to pieces in the second half.
</P>
<P>
United have now broken the premier league's goalscoring record
with 84 from 33 games.
</P>
<P>
The result was a huge psychological boost for United before the
second leg of their Champions League quarter-final against Real
Madrid at Old Trafford on Wednesday. The first leg ended goalless.
</P>
<P>
The European Cup holders have 76 points and, with their
superior goal difference, effectively need 80 to be champions --
the maximum number of points that Liverpool can pick up in their
last six games. They play Wimbledon on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Third-placed Leeds also take on Arsenal on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Fourth-placed Chelsea's hopes of staying in the battle for the
second direct spot in the Champions League were hit by a 1-0
defeat at relegation-theatened Sheffield Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Chelsea, who take on Barcelona away in their Champions League
quarter-final second leg on Tuesday after winning the first leg 3-
1, lost to a 51st minute penalty by Wim Jonk. 
</P>
</TEXT>
