<HEADLINE> Frankfurt Loses to Kaiserslautern in Bundesliga </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Frankfurt remained at the brink of
the relegation after suffering double blows on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The team lost to Kaiserslautern 0-1 and faced a possible two-
point deduction from their total on the standings.
</P>
<P>
Frankfurt had scoring chances in the game and failed to
capitalize on them. The club was also fined by the German soccer
authority DFB for breaking the rules by running heavily into debt.
</P>
<P>
The penalty was imposed after the 1980 UEFA Cup winners were
called before the DFB licensing committee to explain their
finances, which include arrears of $6.8 million.
</P>
<P>
Frankfurt will be docked two points at the end of the season
and risk expulsion from the first division if they stay too much
in the red.
</P>
<P>
Bayern Munich lost to its crosstown rivals 1860 Munich in the
Olympia Stadium. 1860's Martin Max put his team ahead 1-0 in the
22nd minute and seven minutes later Bayern's Mehmet Scholl
equalized with a freekick. Martin Max has scored 16 goals this
season.
</P>
<P>
Jens Jeremies scored an own goal in the 40th minute, handing
1860 the victory.
</P>
<P>
After the defeat Bayern Munich has 61 points and remains on top
due to a superior goal difference over Bayer Leverkusen. Bayer
Leverkusen will play against Arminia Bielefeld tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
The game between Hamburg and Werder Bremen ended goalless and
Hamburg remains in third place with 55 points.
</P>
<P>
Stuttgart defeated Freiburg 1-0 at home. Romanian Viorel Ganea
got the only goal in the 82nd minute, but one minute later he was
sent off with two yellow cards.
</P>
<P>
Two relegation candidates Duisburg and Dortmund met this
afternoon. Dortmund, led by new head coach Udo Lattek could not
yet win a victory.
</P>
<P>
Just after six minutes Marijan Kovacevic put Duisburg to lead
with 1-0. Dortmund's Otto Addo and Christian Woerns each got a
goal in the 13th and 25th minute.
</P>
<P>
Duisburg then equalized through a penalty kick from Michael
Zeyer in the 44th minute. The club still stands at the end of the
league table with 21 points.
</P>
<P>
Collated results:
