BAGHDAD -- U.S. congressman Tony Hall arrived in the Iraqi
capital of Baghdad at 1917 local time (1517 GMT) on Sunday for a
landmark visit to Iraq, the first of its kind by a U.S. congressman
since the 1991 Gulf War.
